    "image_26.jpg": "DIAMOND 💎 VIP PACKAGE now\n📷 Photo\n\n🏀 NBA:\n4% each\n\nWarriors ML ✅",
    "image_27.jpg": "DIAMOND 💎 VIP PACKAGE now\n📷 Photo\n\n🏀 NBA:\n4% each\n\nBucks ML ✅\n\nNuggets ML ❌",
    "image_28.jpg": "PorterPicks Yesterday at 10:00 PM\nBOWL GAME SELECTION for TUESDAY 12/30\n@everyone\n\n⚡\nMUSIC CITY BOWL\n\nTENNESSEE/ILLINOIS\n\nOVER 61.5 (-105)\n\n(4-UNITS) 💰💰💰💰\n\n2:30pm PST - ESPN\n\nTENNESSEE is 6-2 to the OVER/UNDER as a\nFAVORITE and ILLINOIS is 3-1 to the OVER/UNDER as\nan UNDERDOG! Both defenses were very weak\nagainst the pass and on third down this season and\nthese two quarterbacks in Altmyer and Aguilar were\nvery successful this season passing the football.\n\nTo make it even more worse for these defenses, they\nwon’t have a few starters during to opt-outs and\nthese two quarterbacks transfer portal. Tennessee\nalso won’t have a Defensive Coordinator for this game\nas HC Josh Heupel fired Tim Banks and hired Jim\nKnowles from Penn State for next season.\n\nThe TOTAL opened up at 59.5 and has since climbed\ndespite over 75% public tickets and public money on\nthe UNDER. There is still VALUE on the OVER here\nunder the key betting number of 63. 👀\n\nDone reading? Check out other channels.",
    "image_29.jpg": "PorterPicks Yesterday at 10:29 PM\nBOWL GAME SELECTION for TUESDAY 12/30\n(continued)\n\n⚡\nALAMO BOWL\n\nTCU (+7) good to (+6.5) over USC\n\n(3-UNITS) 💰💰💰\n\n6:00pm PST - ESPN\n\nUSC has their three top receivers and Tight End all\nOUT for this game and even though TCU won’t have\nHoover at quarterback, HC Sonny Dykes has had\nplenty of time to get his quarterbacks ready for this\ngame in which he may play two quarterbacks. This\nwas a TCU offense that was once one of the best\noffenses in the country earlier this season and\nperhaps this TCU team comes in aggressive\noffensively against a USC defense that has been\nsuspect all season.\n\nRemember, USC is 0-3 ATS in their last three games\nand 1-4 ATS away from The Memorial Coliseum in LA.\nThis game is being played in the Alamodome in San\nAntonio, TX which is technically a home game for\nTCU being only 4 hours away! 👀\n\n🏈🏈🏈🏈\n\nDone reading? Check out other channels.",
    "image_30.jpg": "PorterPicks 12:36 AM\nBOWL GANE BONUS UNDERDOG SELECTION for\nTUESDAY\n\n⚡\nMUSIC CITY BOWL\n\nILLINOIS (+3.5) over Tennessee\n\n(4-UNITS) 💰💰💰💰\n\n2:30pm PST - ESPN\n\nThe VOLS defense is atrocious! It’s that simple! They\nallowed 28 ppg and close to 400 yards ppg. Illinois\nquarterback Luke Altmyer is going to have plenty of\nsuccess moving the football up and down the field on\nthis Vols defense. The only reason why Tennessee is a\nfavorite in this game is because they represent the\nSEC and the fact this game is being played in\nNashville, TN.\n\nIllinois has played the more tougher strength of\nschedule this season and keep in mind too that\nTennessee has only one victory over one team that’s\nin a Bowl Game this season and that’s Mississippi\nState who has a losing record. With Tennessee not\nhaving a DC and the fact they are already a struggling\ndefense allowing a ton of yards and points, and the\nfact the Vols are only 3-7 ATS in their last 10 games,\nIllinois is the SHARP side in this Bowl Game,\nespecially catching points with the better defense.\n\n🏈🏈🏈🏈\n\nDone reading? Check out other channels."
