    "ocr_texts": [
      "8-Unit Play. Take #694 North Carolina (-12) over Notre Dame (7 p.m., Wednesday, Jan. 21)\n\nI think that Notre Dame is a dead stick. Their season went in the tank the minute that Markus Burton went down for the year. Even with Burton, I had my doubts about this as an NCAA tournament team. Without him they are sunk. Micah Shrewsbury may not make it to the end of the year on the Notre Dame bench. He has been an embarrassment. Whether it was calling out the Irish fans last year, attacking the refs after a Cal loss this year, or just being a dick at the end of the Virginia Tech game last Saturday, he looks like a dead man walking. I think he is losing the locker room as well. They have lost four straight and the losses are getting worse, not better, coming by 15, 12 and 13 points. They are facing a North Carolina team that is in a foul mood. The Tar Heels got swept on their West Coast trip last weekend, falling at Cal and Stanford. Now they are at home and they need a win to get things going. Notre Dame has not played well at Chapel Hill at all, losing by 20, 23, 17, and 42 points in their last four trips. They have only lost by fewer than 11 points here once since the end of 2018. I don't think that Notre Dame is going to be able to handle the size and athleticism of the Tar Heels. I also think the home team is going to be able to set the tempo and that means an up and down game. North Carolina hasn't trucked anyone in a while. This feels like a game where they can empty the tanks and run a tired, worn out Notre Dame team off the court.\n\n1-Unit Play. Take #720 Wichita State (-11.5) over East Carolina (7:30 p.m., Wednesday, Jan. 21)"
